data.name: Digitless World
data.description:
Oh no! You've magically been transported to a world without digits!

You'll need to write a function that evaluates mathematical expressions in plain words like:

```three plus five``` or ```ten divided by two```

and returns the correct answer in in plain words.

You may not use digits at all in your function. Nobody knows what those are.

Rules:

  You only need to evaluate expressions containing whole positive numbers from ```zero``` to ```one hundred```

  They will only evaluate to whole positive numbers from ```zero``` to ```one hundred```.

  You only need to deal with one operator in each expression
  
  operators will be (```plus``` , ```minus```, ```times``` , or ```divided by```).
